data.title: PRESS STATEMENT FROM THE PRIME MINISTER'S OFFICE
data.text:
Official Visit of Senior Minister Goh Chok Tong

to Algeria and Tunisia

1 - 7 April 2006

Senior Minister Goh Chok Tong will make an official visit to Algeria from 1-4 April 2006 and Tunisia from 4-7 April 2006. The visit is part of Singapore's on-going efforts to deepen political and economic engagement with the Middle East and Maghreb countries.

In Algeria, Senior Minister will meet with Prime Minister Ahmed Ouyahia, Algerian Ministers and businessmen. Senior Minister will also attend and deliver remarks at a business seminar organised by the Algerian Ministry of Participations and Promotions of Investments.

In Tunisia, Senior Minister will meet with Prime Minister Mohamed Ghannouchi, Tunisian Ministers and businessmen.

Senior Minister will be accompanied by Minister of State for Foreign Affairs Zainul Abidin Rasheed, Minister of State for National Development Heng Chee How, senior officials and a business delegation.
